cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of mobile eye tracking to assess levels of attention in users interacting with a laptop, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves analyzing changes in pupil size, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential for using the data collected to modify smartphone content and interaction, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
